    "8 The higher the resolution of the map compared to θ E, the better the pixels approximate the size of a point source.",
    "For pixel sizes of < 0.006 θ E (practically point sources), Vernardos and Fluke (2013) found that the minimum size for unbiased maps is 24 × 24 θ E.",
